My brother brought home 3 young skunks after he had discovered them at the dairy barn where he worked and finding the mother skunk had gotten killed by a car by the road by the barn.  The vet said they were too young to care for themselves, so we raised them fully intact (did not alter them in any way so they could still spray) to adulthood.  For starters skunks don't have a natural fear of pretty much anything, people included, so the kits (baby skunks) took right to living in the house with us.  They would pile up in bed with us, along with the dogs, and everybody got along fine until they were grown enough to fend for themselves, and at that point we let them go into the woods behind our house.
